HEADWORD: Unimuscular
<hw>U`ni*mus"cu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets> muscular.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having
only one adductor muscle, and one muscular impression on each valve, as
the oyster; monomyarian.</def>⟦br⟧
